      "uploadedFileId": "5dd261b4-84b6-4765-99bd-f1cb229070f3",
      "summary": "Key points from NLP:\n\n\u2022 1. Introduction to ERP Systems\n\u2022 ERP stands for Enterprise Resource Planning. It is an integrated software solution used to manage and coordinate all the core business functions of an organization within a single unified system. ERP connects departments such as Finance, Human Resources, Sales, Inventory, Production, Procurement and Supply Chain into one platform, helping organizations eliminate duplication, reduce manual work, and improve communication. In today\u2019s competitive environment, ERP systems enhance efficiency and provide real-time visibility, allowing businesses to make faster and better decisions.\n\u2022 The concept of ERP evolved from early Material Requirements Planning (MRP) and Manufacturing Resource Planning (MRP-II) systems. Modern ERP solutions\u2014powered by cloud computing, artificial intelligence (AI), and data analytics\u2014are flexible, scalable, and accessible to organizations of all sizes. Popular systems such as SAP, Oracle ERP Cloud, Microsoft Dynamics 365, Odoo, Tally, and Infor help enterprises streamline operations and achieve sustainable growth by integrating technology with business strategy.\n\u2022 Example: When a customer places an order, ERP automatically updates sales records, inventory levels, production plans, and accounting data without manual input.\n\u2022 Popular ERP Software: SAP ERP, Oracle ERP Cloud, Microsoft Dynamics 365, Odoo, Tally ERP, and Infor.\n\u2022 Centralized Database: ERP uses a single database that stores information accessible to all authorized departments.\n\u2022 Functions Covered: Accounting, manufacturing, procurement, sales, logistics, inventory, and customer relationship management.\n\u2022 Evolution: Originated from Material Requirements Planning (MRP) systems in the 1960s \u2192 evolved into MRP-II (Manufacturing Resource Planning) \u2192 modern ERP integrates all business operations.",
      "uploadedFileName": "software content.docx",
      "uploadedFilePath": "uploads\\5dd261b4-84b6-4765-99bd-f1cb229070f3.docx",
      "rawTextPreview": "1. Introduction to ERP Systems\nERP stands for Enterprise Resource Planning. It is an integrated software solution used to manage and coordinate all the core business functions of an organization within a single unified system. ERP connects departments such as Finance, Human Resources, Sales, Inventory, Production, Procurement and Supply Chain into one platform, helping organizations eliminate duplication, reduce manual work, and improve communication. In today\u2019s competitive environment, ERP syst"
